groups with different exposures and no comparisons between groups with different outcomes.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>3</td>\n                <td                <td>A non-comparative study design in which two or more participants are evaluated in a single group (or cohort).</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n 2</td>\n                <td>Includes controlled clinical studies conducted to evaluate the effectiveness of the drug for a particular indication or indications in participants with the disease or <td>2</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  SEVCO:01001\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801001\"> </a>\n                </td>\n                <td>Interventional research</td>\n                <td>A study design in which an independent variable (an exposure or intervention) is prospectively assigned or modified by the investigator to evaluate a response in the dependent variable (an effect or outcome).</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>3</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    SEVCO:01003\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801003\"> </a>\n                </td>\n                <td>randomized assignment</td>\n                <td>An interventional study design in which an independent variable (an exposure or intervention) is prospectively assigned or modified by random chance to separate groups.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>4</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      SEVCO:01006\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801006\"> </a>\n                </td>\n                <td>simple randomization</td>\n                <td>A randomized assignment in which each participant has the same prespecified likelihood of being assigned to a group as all other participants, independent of the assignment of any other participant.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>4</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      SEVCO:01007\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801007\"> </a>\n                </td>\n                <td>stratified randomization</td>\n                <td>A randomized assignment in which participants are stratified into groups based on prognostic variables and then randomized into balanced treatment groups</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>4</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      SEVCO:01008\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801008\"> </a>\n                </td>\n                <td>block randomization</td>\n                <td>A randomized assignment in which a pre-specified number of subjects is assigned to a block containing the same pre-specified ratio of group assignments in random order.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>4</td>\n                <td              <td>A randomized assignment in which a participant’s group assignment probability is adjusted based on any factor such that the likelihood of assignment is not the same for all participants.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>3</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    SEVCO:01005\n                  <a independent variable (an exposure or intervention) is prospectively assigned or modified by methods other than random chance to separate groups.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>4</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      SEVCO:01004\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801004\"> </a>\n                </td>\n                <td>Quasi-Randomized assignment</td>\n                <td>An interventional study design with a method of allocation that is not limited to random chance but is intended to produce similar baseline groups for experimentation.</td>\n              </tr>\n              <tr>\n                <td>3</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">    SEVCO:01029\n                  <a      <tr>\n                <td>4</td>\n                <td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">      SEVCO:01032\n                  <a name=\"research-study-classifiers-SEVCO.5801032\"> </a>\n
